---
import ContentLayout from '../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
---

<ContentLayout title="About" authorName="About">
  <div class="space-y-12">
    <header>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:text-5xl">About</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">Alongside my interests in software and data engineering, I like to enjoy sports, entertainment, and a good sandwich.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-12">
      <!-- Sports -->
      <section class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 flex items-center gap-3">
          <i class="fas fa-table-tennis-paddle-ball text-blue-600"></i> Sports
        </h2>
        <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
          <ul>
            <li>
              I grew up loving team sports while playing <strong>soccer</strong> <i class="fas fa-futbol" style="color: #1f512b;"></i> and watching <strong>football</strong> <i class="fas fa-football-ball" style="color: #511f1f;"></i>. Nowadays, you'll find me occassionally playing <strong>pickleball</strong> <i class="fas fa-table-tennis" style="color: #0fcc84;"></i> and shanking <strong>golf balls</strong> <i class="fas fa-golf-ball" style="color: #c0c0c9;"></i>. 
            </li>
            <li>
              As a college student, I served as the Vice President for the <a href="https://www.instagram.com/sbaucirvine" target="_blank">UCI Sports Business Association</a> and as a member of the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/TennisClubatUCI/" target="_blank">UCI Club Tennis</a> travel team <i class="fas fa-baseball-ball" style="color: #dff24a;"></i>. Go Eaters!
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Eagle Scout -->
      <section class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 flex items-center gap-3">
          <i class="fas fa-medal text-blue-600"></i> Eagle Scout
        </h2>
        <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
          <ul>
            <li>
              Alhough I've only kept a few of the outdoor skills from being in Boy Scouts for 7 years, I attribute much of my desire for organization and efficiency from watching my Troop's strong adult and scout leaders.
            </li>
            <li>
              Completing my <strong>Eagle Project</strong> taught me the importance of <strong>"leadership, leadership, leadership"</strong> and specifically the amount of planning and delegation required to accomplish big tasks.
            </li>
            <li>
              Thanks to Scouting I will never forget to set <strong>SMART Goals</strong> that are specific, measurable, attainable, relevent, and timely.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-headings:font-bold prose-a:text-blue-600 prose-a:hover:text-blue-800">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-music" style="color: #6d4d9d;"></i> Music</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://open.spotify.com/playlist/0fXEEXQLRVRKN68i7iCmtI?si=1bd4cab161064d33">Upbeat Alternative Rock</a> is my jam <i class="fas fa-headphones-alt" style="color: #f57d3d;"></i></li>
          <li>On my <a href="/music">YouTube channel</a> I play <strong>ukulele and guitar</strong> covers of my favorite songs from tv shows and anime</li>
          <li>Check out a <strong>tier list of my favorite artists</strong> at -> <a href="https://www.me-db.app/user/e_lee538/artists">me-db.app/user/e_lee538/artists</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

  </div>
</ContentLayout>
